  "texts": [
    "If we stay with our example, the model could be given the context \"I'm feeling\" and assign the same probability to the possible outputs \"good\" or \"bad\" because the context here gives no indication of which of these is more likely to fit.",
    "However, if the context says \"I was praised.",
    "I'm feeling\", then the model should assign a higher probability to \"good\".",
    "Then a task-specific fine-tuning can be carried out -hence the P. For example, when writing with ChatGPT, you can recognize thumbs up and thumbs down symbols under the answers.",
    "Information from this feedback is then used to improve 9 the model via reinforcement learning foot_3."
  ],
